{"article_id":"ORYRJ2ZaYCHsVQzy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"California may have swiftly passed the Presidential Tax Transparency and Accountability Act ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"forcing President Trump and other presidential primary candidates to disclose their tax returns","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"if they want to be on the 2020 ballot ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"but the challenges have already begun .","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"Judicial Watch announced Monday","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"that it filed a federal lawsuit against the state on behalf of four California voters","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"to block the law ' s implementation .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"If left unchallenged ,","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"the law would force those","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"who wish to appear on California ' s March 3 , 2020 presidential primary ballot","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"to publicly disclose their tax returns for the last five years ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"turning them over to California ' s secretary of state by November 26 .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Former California Gov . Jerry Brown vetoed a similar measure last year ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"questioning the constitutionality of such a law","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"and arguing","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"that it sets a \" slippery slope precedent \"","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"that could pave the way","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"for requiring other types of documents from candidates .","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"\" Today we require tax returns ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"but what would be next ? ''","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Brown asked at the time .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"`` Five years of health records ?","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"A certified birth certificate ?","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"High school report cards ?","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"And will these requirements vary","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"depending on which political party is in power . ''","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The plaintiffs are ideologically diverse ;","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"two are Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"one is an independent ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"and one is a Democrat .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"`` No state or federal law has ever mandated","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"that presidential candidates disclose their tax returns","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"to qualify","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"or appear on a ballot , ''","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"the federal complaint says .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"`` The voluntary release of presidential candidates ' tax returns is a recent , and partial , phenomenon ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"notwithstanding a current media narrative","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"suggesting otherwise . ''","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"Judicial Watch President Tom Fitton said","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"the \" nonpartisan concern \" is \" about the state running roughshod","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"and attempting to amend the Constitution on its own . \"","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"\" California politicians , in their zeal","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"to attack President Trump ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"passed a law","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"that also unconstitutionally victimizes California voters , ''","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Fitton said .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"`` It is an obvious legal issue","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"that a state can ' t amend the U.S. Constitution","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"by adding qualifications","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"in order to run for president . ''","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"The Constitution only requires","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"a presidential candidate be at least 35 years old , a natural born citizen ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"and have lived in the U.S. for at least 14 years .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"In signing the law ,","depth":4},{"id":54,"text":"Newsom released a statement","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"arguing","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"that California is \" well within its constitutional right \"","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"to require the tax returns ,","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"issuing statements from three attorneys","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"arguing the same .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"`` SB 27 ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"which requires","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"that presidential candidates disclose tax returns ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"is constitutional .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"It does not keep any candidate from being on the ballot","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"so long as he or she complies with a simple requirement","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"that is meant to provide California voters crucial information , ''","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"wrote University of California , Berkeley law school dean Erwin Chemerinsky .","depth":4},{"id":68,"text":"`` This is the state","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"acting to make sure","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"that its voters have information","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"that might be very important to them","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"when they cast their ballots","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"as to who they want to be President of the United States . ''","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Judicial Watch clearly disagrees ,","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"with Fitton noting","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"`` the courts can ' t stop this abusive law fast enough . \"","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":153,"left":114,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":80,"right":113,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":80,"left":79,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":79,"left":0,"right":78,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":78,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":82,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":82,"left":4,"right":81,"relation":"attribution","nuc